description: Decimal expansion of fifth root of 3.
references: N. J. A. Sloane and Simon Plouffe, The Encyclopedia of Integer Sequences, Academic Press, 1995 (includes this sequence).
links: Harry J. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..20000
maple: Digits := 200: it := evalf(3^(1/5)/10, 200)-floor(evalf(3^(1/5)/10, 200)): for i from 1 to 150 do printf(`%d,`,floor(10*it)): it := 10*it-floor(10*it): od:
prog: (PARI) { default(realprecision, 20080); x=3^(1/5); for (n=1, 20000, d=floor(x); x=(x-d)*10; write("b005532.txt", n, " ", d)); } \\ _Harry J. Smith_, May 12 2009
crossrefs: Cf. A003117 (continued fraction). - _Harry J. Smith_, May 12 2009
author: _N. J. A. Sloane_
extensions: More terms from _James A. Sellers_, Feb 19 2001
